  2. Every fifth vs every fourth — not a bug                                                                                                                                                                                           
                                                            
  With a 4-sided QUAD polygon, both rules produce identical results at 1–2 subdivision levels (both show 25%). They only diverge at 3 levels (64 children: every-fourth shows 16, every-fifth shows 13). The user just needs deeper    
  subdivision to see the difference.                        
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       
  3. PTW (PolysTransformWhole) — logically present, semantics differ from Scala                                                                                                                                                        
   
  The Swift implementation exists and is structurally correct. The main semantic difference from Scala: Scala overwrites pTW_transform values in-place with random values then applies one combined transform; Swift applies the       
  deterministic transform first and then applies random components as additional steps. Both should produce visible output when non-identity values are used. If the user sees no effect at all, most likely the base transform is
  still identity (scale=1, translation=0) with no random flags enabled — that's expected behaviour, not a bug. Needs testing with a real configured project.                                                                           
                                                            
  4. PTP (PolysTransformPoints) — major missing feature, not implemented                                                                                                                                                               
   
  Swift's applyPoints only does random per-point translation. Scala's PTP runs the full TransformSet: five distinct algorithms — ExteriorAnchors, CentralAnchors, AnchorsLinkedToCentre, OuterControlPoints, InnerControlPoints. None  
  of these exist in Swift. This is the largest item: each is a non-trivial algorithm that needs porting from loom_engine/src/main/scala/org/loom/transform/.


